py significant political and cultural roles.Christopher Morash explores the stories and political trajectories of an acting-Governor of the Territory of Montana and Union Army General, a Confederate newspaper owner, a Premier of Victoria, and many other important figures. Despite their divergent trajectories, these individuals applied many of the same ideas that they had developed during their original Irish political project to their respective nations and movements. Young Ireland is a vital new perspective in the field of Irish diaspora studies, highlighting the impact the Young Ireland generation had on emerging democracies and international debates, both in spite of and because of their defeat and dispersion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aIrish diasporaxHistoryy19th century. 0aIrishxPolitical activityzForeign countriesxHistoryy19th century. 0aIrishzForeign countriesxIntellectual life. 0aNationalistszIrelandxHistoryy19th century. 0aTransnationalism. 0aYoung Ireland movement. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Ireland.2bisacsh  aAustralia.  aCitizenship.  aClass.  aCommunications.  aDemocracy.  aDiaspora.  aEmpire.  aImperialism.  aIntellectual history.  aIreland.  aIrish histor.  aManifest Destiny.  aMasculinity.  aMinority Rights.  aNationalism.  aNativism.  aTasmania.  aTransportation.  aUnited States of America.  aYoung America.  ay Political thought.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle i